TODO: Calendar view with account balance (or sum of selected accounts balances) for each day with coloring when balance drops below zero. Competitive applications have this feature.  BUG: Recurring transactions without expiration date are automatically created for 2 years in the future. Recurring transactions with expiration date set are created however until expiration date (which can be more than 2 years forward). This results in incorrect account balance, empty transaction list, faulty diagrams after two years. This is a serious fault which has to be fixed.
replyContent:
The recurring transactions are always created for 2 years in the future. Every time the app starts, the app checks if new recurring transactions must be created. So you have always your recurring transactions for the next 2 years.
If you want it directly longer, just set an expiration date in a far future. Please send further questions by email.

content: Great app. Takes time to get used to and is essentially a glorified auto ledger. But it's great. I'd like to be able to label previous search filters into groups or categories such as weekly or pay cycle (fortnightly). At the. Kment labelling a search filters title actually affects the filter itself. I like to manage my expenses in weekly chunks or fortnightly chunks. So an easier way to swap between the default monthly view would be great.  2. I wish there was a way to toggle my budgets as expenses. As it stands this app is great for projecting income. But this projected income doesn't take into account your budget limit. For example. If I set a budget of 140 dollars for food, it would be a great to be able to toggle that budget so that the highest value (140) is inserted as a temporary  transaction. content: I had installed, tried, & subsequently uninstalled 5 other highly- rated apps before i got to this one.  My Budget Book makes it possible to sort/ view/ plan/ manage your finances in pretty much any way you'd want.  There are of course apps which make an automatic real-time feed from various accounts possible, across all your devices,  which this one does not have.  What you get in return is the knowledge that some developer you don't know is not looking at (and selling) your financial data. So yes, there's some compromise in terms of ease, but the workaround for this is easy enough, and it takes me less than 2 minutes to get the same version of my finances on both my phone and tablet.   The app allows you to manipulate, search, plan in most/all ways you'd want to... and the developer is very responsive to any queries/ enhancement ideas you might have. I'm no financial dummy, but was too disorganised, and too overwhelmed at the prospect of getting organised. I could see immediately that this would help and it has done. Now I am organised, I can also appreciate the flexibility it gives for those people who were already organised, and who just want a straightforward, flexible means of staying on top of things - in a way that (unlike spreadsheets) is easy to view on a phone or small tablet.
Amazing app, complete overview of your daily, monthly and yearly spending, really helpful , easy to use, help track and review spending and saving if necessary Well done developers 👍👌👏

content: Recently was looking around for a good finance application. After some fiddling around with various apps, this app is the one closes to my wants and needs. As of now, I use it daily and it's one of my most used apps.  - Usability: The app is  lightweight and very responsive, it takes maybe a day of use do to the more basic UI interface, but it's intuitive enough for me. Also the widgets for fast entry of expenses is very handy.  - Safety & Privacy: YES, finally an budget app without cloud / server synchronization. Better yet, the network connection for the app is disabled so there is no chance for a MITM attack. For protection of the app itself, it's possible to set a long password for access, and every time your phone goes to sleep, it asks for it. Not sure about the actual encryption of the database itself, info could be included in the manual.    - Interface: Quite basic and simple, which makes it fast in use. It's maybe not the nicest or most fresh UI out there, but for me it's all I need.  - Else: Very fast response (<1 hour every question) from the developer and an extensive manual make me trust this app and developer. This app gets 5* and deserves your attention.

To cap this, I was looking for a similar app on Android that would help me keep track of past, present and future transactions that allowed flexibility to change recurring payments when a single event differed from the norm and showed the account balance for each day, even future days where recurring or one-off transactions were setup.  After downloading, trying and uninstalling 6 apps, I finally found this one, My Budget Book.  Before going through the time involved in inputting all my data again, I emailed the developer to check it was going to do what I needed it to do.  The answer came back the same day and with assurane that it would achieve what I wanted.    A couple of  helpful emails later, he had helped me setup the app exactly how I needed it and I have to say, it is far better than the previous one I had on my iPhone.  It is certainly worth the small amount charged for this app as it is very flexible.  I would recommend this app to anyone who likes to be able to see how any transaction would afffect the balances on the account at any given time, including future or expected payments.
Easy to use

For example, to add recurring salary you have to use something called "standing order". If you live in the U.S.  like me, then you have no idea what that is. I had to go on wikipedia to figure out its a "recurring payment". So you have to use Standing Orders to configure anything recurring, including transfers, revenues, and bill payments. What really had me pulling my hair out is that you cant see a list of what you create. Instead you have to look at the transaction reports to find what you created, but like I mentioned earlier, good luck with that. The final straw is how daily balance is presented. My whole purpose for getting this is to be able to predict how much money I will have on any specific day in the future to make wise spending decisions.  However it will only show you the debits and credits for a specific day but not the available balance on that specific day (look at the photos). And there are no help files whatsoever. You're on your own. Don't waste your time or money on this crap.

The date format is determined on the basis of language and country of your phone's settings.

The administration of the optional field "Payment type" will be implemented with an update.

content: Easy to use, easy to adapt, very worth it for every dollar we spending. With your accounting skill and little bit improvisation, I can make a balance sheet for my self....hehehehe and i think this apps need manual or guide books. After all the developer did great job here!!!
I like it. Its very good and functional. Draws graphs and its flexible to use
Basic but not too much- easy to use and template function handy. Search/ monitor functions even more so.
Great app to manage your finances ans report on where it all goes. Used it to budget a holiday in Tonga as well.

This was exactly what I was looking for in a budgeting app - you can import CSV files, catagorise and see what you have been spending your money on with some good graphs.     A couple of notes on importing CSV - you need to have the exact headings that the app uses in your input file, otherwise it won't work. The best way to do this is to create a dummy invoice then export it.    Emailed the dev a couple of questions, got back to me in under an hour, brilliant!

After I tried few budget planner apps who failed to meet my needs I found this great app. The only problem is that it hasn't my currency. After I emailed the dev about this issue, he replied to me within hours that my currency will be added in the next update. For those who are looking for a good budget manager I recommend them to try this app. You'll find that you don't need to search for anything else.

I installed this app last week. Initially it took a short bit to get used to where everything was and how it worked, but it was pretty quick to get used to. The app could use a 'help' or 'how-to' document so that users could get started and understand its use more quickly, but that's just a thought. I noticed a few things that could use improvement during my first few days of use and the Dev always responded to my emails within a few hours letting me know what he thought of my ideas and whether or not he was already incorporating them into an update. I am highly pleased with the app overall. I am still in search of something to mimic some of the concepts in Quicken or MS Money for my phone, which Is why I installed this app. It does lack a line-by-line running balance which would be highly useful. It really just shows, based on the debits and credits you enter, where you'll be for the overall month as a positive or negative balance. That is nice, but a monthly scale is a bit too broad because in the middle of the month you may dip near the negative on not be aware of it just looking at the 'Bank Statement' tab. I still love the app though! Good job dev! (Samsung Galaxy Nexus).
Now can manage my money effectively.i  suggest to make option for excel file, so we can print and make hard copy.tq
Please add more currency, It'll be fine if the UI still in other UI. but I need my currency for this app!!

I wish all devs are like this one. Bought the app and quickly realized that it's missing the Indonesian Rupiah currency. Emailed the dev asking for rupiah to be included just trying my luck and whaddaya know, he replied! Said he'll include it in next update. My 1st experience of having a dev reply back to me. App is great, too, many functionalities, great visual and absolutely does the same work as EasyMoney or YNAB or Mint (which I can't even find in market) ... for $1.98. FTW.

My last suggestion was implemented within a week, if only all developers gave the same level of support. One last suggestion though, I'm paid weekly every Thursday but when I set a standing order to show my weekly income, the day it goes in seems to get messed up. Perhaps change it so that you can choose how standing orders reoccur. Thanks again for a great app.
It's a very useful app. I love it:)
